The economic development of the caravans to the villages will be broadcast through CCTV Financial Channel, Central Broadcasting Corporation, China Communications Broadcasting Corporation, CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, live television will be completed mainly in CCTV's noon news program "Tenka Financial" (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 12:00-13:00 ), CCTV's golden-film news column "Economic Information Joint Broadcast" will open a poverty alleviation report column (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 20:30-21:30 ).
At the same time, the caravan will carry out a live broadcast of each village in the CCTV financial client for up to one hour, viewers can download the CCTV financial app, watch live, participate in the raffle activities.
In terms of technology applications and broadcasting room design, "Go Village Live to Watch the Eradication of Poverty" bravely broke through and pioneered the "Outdoor New Media Tent Car".
The car is equipped with 5G new media mobile cloud broadcasting system, using 5G+4K/8K+AI technology to realize the organic combination of online and offline, large screen and small screen, television broadcasting.
It has a three-channel broadcasting area, which consists of a 12-metre-long, 2.55-metre-wide and 3.98-metre-high container with a hydraulic self-expanding structure that can be turned up to 120 degrees.
The broadcast area can also be expanded automatically, and an external expansion platform, with an area of more than 50 square meters, can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
At present, Dongchuan District of Kunming City is already hot in summer, and more hot than the weather is easy to relocate the poverty-relief workshop next to the resettlement point.
"Now, as soon as you get out of your home, you can go into the factory and make money," said Lu Ling, an employee at ASF Electronics and Technology Co. in Kunming. "It's thanks to free vocational skills training organized by the trade union.
Entering the Dongchuan District Copper City street electronic components processing poverty alleviation workshop, a fireworks display of busy scenes into the eye.
Lu Ling, in her 40s, is a single mother who carries her children alone and takes care of older parents.
At her most difficult time, the Dongchuan District General Union helped to come up with ideas and ideas, and "carried charcoal in the snow" before running.
Starting in 2018, Lü Ling has benefited from support policies such as housing, schooling, social security, employment, and support payments from trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and are employed, and she herself has got a job and income after participating in skill training, and has been out of poverty by the end of April.
It is reported that Dongchuan District General Organization to help combat poverty and strengthen special skills training project, is part of the Yunnan Provincial General Trade Union skills training work.
The district summarized the characteristics of the hard-working workers in the district who could easily help with poverty alleviation and resettlement, conducted in-depth investigations to understand the training needs and determined the types of training, and planned to train 450 people in the near future, such as electricians, welders and spotters.
Recently, Agricultural Bank of Yunnan Menglian County branch staff member Li Yi to the county union wrote a heartfelt thank you letter.
In her letter, she expressed her sincere gratitude to the union for the financial support she received from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the hard-working staff file.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi completed her schooling successfully.
Since 2016, 3809 households have been lifted out of poverty through the system of guarantees and precise assistance.
The successful emancipation of the Luling family and Li Yi is an epitome of the Yunnan Trade Union's promotion of the emancipation of difficult workers.
According to the introduction of Yunnan Provincial General Trade Union Law and Human Rights Protection Department Staff Section Kai Yuan, the provincial general strengthened the dynamic management of hardship workers' files, promoted normalization of filing work, timely integration of hardship workers who meet the filing requirements into the support system; broadened the application channels for hardship workers, using WeChat to open the online application hardship workers filing service platform, facilitated hardship workers to promptly voluntarily declare.
During the epidemic, Yunnan province allocated more than 13 million yuan to send warmth funds to help workers with difficulties in workplaces to alleviate the pressure on their lives.In accordance with the standard of 2,000 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in workplaces at the national level and 1,500 yuan per household for workers with difficulties in workplaces at the provincial level, more than 6,000 households at the national level and more than 1,000 households at the provincial level implemented special warmth condolence activities for workers with difficulties in workplaces.
At the same time, the provincial headquarters interacts with the departments of human rights and social welfare and various Internet recruitment platforms such as Jilian Recruiting, pushing the recruitment information to workers in difficulty, and providing employment advice, employment guidance and other services.
